Boil a full #kettle{}. Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Jasmine rice{150%g} and cook for ~{12-13%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, trim the @cucumber{1/2}. Use a #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the cucumber, stopping at the seeds.

Pop the cucumber ribbons into a small #bowl{} with the @rice vinegar{15%ml} and @sugar for pickling{1} (see pantry for amount).

Add a pinch of @salt{pinch}, mix together, then set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and @sliced mushrooms{80%g}. Fry until the mince is browned and the mushrooms are tender, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break up the mince as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

When the beef is browned, stir in the @ginger puree{15%g} and garlic. Fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @miso paste{15%g}, @ketjap manis{25%ml}, @honey{15%g} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for amount) to the beef. TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Stir to combine and bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened slightly, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Taste and add more salt and pepper if needed.

When the rice is ready, carefully pour the pickling liquid from the cucumber into the rice and stir to combine.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}, then top with the miso beef and sauce.

Serve the pickled cucumber alongside.

> Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Japanese Style Sticky Miso Beef in just 20 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.